JOHANNESBURG - The Department of International Relations (Dirco) has confirmed that Leigh-Ann Naidoo has been released by Israeli authorities. READ: SA woman detained in Israel pleads for government intervention It's believed the activist is currently on her way home. Naidoo had been part of a group trying to oppose the blockade on Gaza. She and a group of female activists had travelled there by boat. Residents in Gaza held protests after they were detained. Hamas, which governs the troubled region, also spoke out, describing the arrests as an act of war. Before Leigh-Ann Naidoo left for Gaza her father shared this piece on Palestinian solidarity. #ReleaseLeighAnn https://t.co/Lkp0YMHP7U eNCA